<p>This instance of class <code>AuthorizationRequest</code> is created during HTTP request, params are sent in query string.</p>  <pre><code>@RequestMapping(value = "/authorize", method = {RequestMethod.GET, RequestMethod.POST})     public String authorize(             @Valid AuthorizationRequest authorizationRequest,             BindingResult result     ) { </code></pre>  <p>I would like to use this code, this is an example parameter from <code>AuthorizationRequest</code> class:</p>  <pre><code>@NotEmpty @JsonProperty("client_id") private String clientId; </code></pre>  <p>but new instance has a filed <code>clientId</code> empty, because in query string there is a value for this parameter under <code>client_id</code> parameter.</p>  <p>Is there some way how to tell Spring which parameter from HTTP request should use for one particular field of created instance? I need to solve problem with different naming <code>clientId and</code>client_id`.</p>